<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="011" project="spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Add ProblemDetails 404 shape per ADR-019 + integration test</title>
    <phase>1: §1.7 Stable Codes Migration</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>004</dependencies>
    <blocks>013</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, testing, ADR-019</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Endpoint shape change + new integration test; tags include 'bff-api' + 'testing'; not a new endpoint surface (010 added it); STANDARD per task-execute Step 0.5</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>1-A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Ensure the `GET /api/ai/playbooks/by-code/{code}` endpoint returns an RFC 7807 ProblemDetails response shape on 404 (code not found) per ADR-019. Add an integration test asserting the response shape (`type`, `title`, `status`, `detail`, `instance`). This is independent of task 010 (endpoint mapping) and task 012 (WorkspaceOptions extension) — operates on a separate response path.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in ASP.NET Core ProblemDetails + xUnit integration testing.</role>

  <goal>
    `GET /api/ai/playbooks/by-code/nonexistent-code` returns HTTP 404 with content-type `application/problem+json` and an RFC 7807 body. Integration test in `tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/` asserts the shape. ProblemDetails `type` URI follows existing Spaarke convention; `title` is human-readable; `detail` includes the missing code.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-01 acceptance + ADR-019. Task 010 stands up the `/by-code/` endpoint; this task ensures the 404 path conforms to the RFC 7807 ProblemDetails contract that Spaarke clients (PCF, code-pages, agents) expect. ProblemDetails on 404 lets clients distinguish "playbook not found" from generic errors without parsing free-text strings.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/PlaybookEmbeddingEndpoints.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/ProblemDetails/</file>
      <file>tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">404 response MUST follow RFC 7807 ProblemDetails shape; content-type `application/problem+json`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">Minimal API — use `Results.Problem(...)` or existing Spaarke ProblemDetails factory; do NOT introduce a Controller.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">ProblemDetails `detail` field MAY include the requested code (it is user-supplied input, not memory content); MUST NOT include user message text or memory facts.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task BFF publish-size measurement required; expect ≤0.1 MB delta.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Test update obligation (CLAUDE.md §10 F) — add integration test asserting RFC 7807 shape.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-001-minimal-api.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-019-problemdetails.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-029-bff-publish-hygiene.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/api.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/testing.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/api/endpoint-definition.md</file>
      <file>docs/procedures/testing-and-code-quality.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Inspect `Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/PlaybookEmbeddingEndpoints.cs` — find the `/by-code/` mapping from task 010. Locate the 404 / lookup-miss branch.</step>
    <step order="2">Inspect existing Spaarke ProblemDetails infrastructure (e.g., `Infrastructure/ProblemDetails/` or convention helpers) to reuse `type` URI prefix + title format.</step>
    <step order="3">Replace the 404 return with `Results.Problem(detail: $"Playbook with code '{code}' not found.", statusCode: 404, type: "...", title: "Playbook Not Found", instance: $"/api/ai/playbooks/by-code/{code}")` (or call existing factory).</step>
    <step order="4">Create integration test `tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/PlaybookByCodeProblemDetailsTests.cs` asserting: 404 status, `application/problem+json` content-type, JSON body has `type`, `title`, `status`, `detail`, `instance` fields, `detail` contains the requested code.</step>
    <step order="5">Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` + `dotnet test tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/` — both pass.</step>
    <step order="6">Measure BFF publish size: `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`; record delta in handoff note.</step>
    <step order="7">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 011 → ✅.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">PlaybookEmbeddingEndpoints.cs + existing ProblemDetails infrastructure</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Modify 404 return path</tool>
    <tool name="Write">Create new integration test file</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">dotnet build / test / publish</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/PlaybookEmbeddingEndpoints.cs — 404 returns ProblemDetails</output>
    <output type="test">tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/PlaybookByCodeProblemDetailsTests.cs — asserts RFC 7807 shape</output>
    <output type="docs">notes/handoffs/011-bff-publish-delta.md — publish size delta</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`GET /api/ai/playbooks/by-code/nonexistent-code-xyz` returns HTTP 404.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Response content-type is `application/problem+json`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Response body has fields: `type`, `title`, `status`, `detail`, `instance`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`detail` field includes the requested code string.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Integration test exits 0.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`dotnet build` exits 0; publish-size delta reported and within NFR-01 thresholds.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Coordinate with task 010 (endpoint mapping) — if 010 already added a ProblemDetails 404, this task simplifies to "add the integration test and verify". Do NOT re-author the endpoint. The 404 path is the only response shape this task owns; success (200) shape is governed by task 010.
  </notes>

